OL,3,CJapanese man acquitted of murder after
OL,4,Cspending 46 years on death row
OL,6,FHakamada was convicted of murder in
OL,7,Fthe 1966 killing of a company manager
OL,8,Fand three of his family members, and
OL,9,Fsetting a fire to their central Japan
OL,10,Fhome. He was sentenced to death in
OL,11,F1968, but was not executed due to
OL,12,Flengthy appeals and the retrial
OL,13,Fprocess.
OL,15,FHe spent 48 years behind bars ` most
OL,16,Fof them on death row ` making him the
OL,17,Fworld's longest-serving death row
OL,18,Finmate.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/11
