OL,3,CJapanese man acquitted of murder after
OL,4,Cspending 46 years on death row
OL,6,FDefense lawyers and earlier retrial
OL,7,Fdecisions said the blood samples did
OL,8,Fnot match Hakamada's DNA, and trousers
OL,9,Fthat prosecutors submitted as evidence
OL,10,Fwere too small for Hakamada and did
OL,11,Fnot fit when he tried them on.
OL,13,FJapan and the United States are the
OL,14,Fonly two countries in the Group of
OL,15,FSeven advanced nations that retain
OL,16,Fcapital punishment. A survey by the
OL,17,FJapanese government showed an
OL,18,Foverwhelming majority of the public
OL,19,Fsupport executions.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/11
