OL,3,CJapanese man acquitted of murder after
OL,4,Cspending 46 years on death row
OL,6,FExecutions are carried out in secrecy
OL,7,Fin Japan and prisoners are not
OL,8,Finformed of their fate until the
OL,9,Fmorning they are hanged. In 2007,
OL,10,FJapan began disclosing the names of
OL,11,Fthose executed and some details of
OL,12,Ftheir crimes, but disclosures are
OL,13,Fstill limited.
OL,15,FSupporters say Hakamada's nearly half-
OL,16,Fcentury detention has taken a toll on
OL,17,Fhis mental health. Most of his time
OL,18,Fbehind bars was spent in solitary
OL,19,Fconfinement, in fear of execution. He
OL,20,Fspent a total of 48 years in prison,
OL,21,Fmore than 45 of them on death row.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/11
